HEADWORD: Stablish
<hw>Stab"lish</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧b"l⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[Aphetic form of <ets>establish</ets>.]</ety> <def>To settle
permanently in a state; to make firm; to establish; to fix.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>2 Sam. vii. 13.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
